#Text=Sandra Fluke gives keynote speech at Nebraska women 's health event
#Text=Thursday , December 6 , 2012
#Text=Women 's rights advocate and Georgetown University Law Center graduate Sandra Fluke was the keynote speaker at a women 's health event Tuesday night in Nebraska .
#Text=Sandra Fluke ( 2012 )
#Text=Image : nmogburn .
#Text=Fluke was the headliner in Lincoln , Nebraska at the Rococo Theatre for the annual fundraiser of Planned Parenthood of the Heartland , titled : " The Big Event : Courage — No Matter What " .
#Text=She currently resides in Los Angeles , California with her fiancé and " Mr. President " , their pet dog .
#Text=After graduating cum laude with her J.D. degree this past May , Fluke successfully took and passed the bar exam in July and is now an attorney .
#Text=It ’s uplifting and heartening to see how many people really care about the issues I ’m talking about .
#Text=— Sandra Fluke

#Text=In an interview with the Lincoln Journal Star , Fluke reflected on her role as a public figure and her ability to contribute to the contribute to the discourse about women 's rights , " It 's uplifting and heartening to see how many people really care about the issues I ’m talking about . "
#Text=Fluke observed , " I think it 's also allowed me to give a voice and shine a light on the work that a lot of people are doing . "
#Text=Fluke 's speech centered on women 's rights , women 's healthcare , and the Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act .
#Text=She stressed the importance of women 's issues in the recent election for U.S. President :
#Text=" This year , something changed in our national conversation about women ’s health ... .

#Text=Planned Parenthood intern and University of Nebraska-Lincoln student Emily Schiltz commented on landing Fluke as the keynote speaker ,  She is definitely the biggest person we 've had in a long time . "

column1: #Text=" I feel like she walks the walk rather than talk the talk , " said Planned Parenthood intern and journalism student Audrey Nance .
#Text=Fluke indicated her intention was to persevere in speaking about issues she thinks important :
#Text=" I think my ultimate goal is giving a voice to people who do n't always have one . "
#Text=She has been named as a candidate by Time magazine in a November 26 announcement , for their Person of the Year .
#Text=Time concluded Fluke helped give U.S. President Barack Obama an edge in his presidential re-election campaign .
#Text=Fluke was a featured speaker on September 5 at the 2012 Democratic National Convention in Charlotte , North Carolina .
#Text=Fluke spoke to attendees at the convention about the consequences for women of electing Republican candidate for U.S. President , Mitt Romney , over incumbent President Barack Obama .
#Text=Fluke has campaigned with President Obama in his bid for re-election .
#Text=She was recognized April 22 with the Stand Up for Choice Award .

#Text=Fluke was given the Stand Up for Choice Award at the " Third Annual Multi-Generational Brunch " of the organization NARAL Pro-Choice America which was held in New York City ( NYC ) , New York in the United States .
#Text=Fluke received a nomination in March as a candidate for Time magazine 's 100 most influential people in the world .
#Text=The list is released annually as a special edition of Time magazine , titled Time 100 .
#Text=She gave testimony to the US Congress on February 23 before the House Democratic Steering and Policy Committee at a hearing about women 's health and contraception .
#Text=She also worked for Sanctuary for Families in NYC which worked to crack down on human trafficking and domestic violence .
